   Do this arr's length times:
      Remember that n is item i in arr
      When n is 0, then:
         Add result to "Zero"
      But, if not:
         When n is 1, then:
            Add result to "One"
         But, if not:
            When n is 2, then:
               Add result to "Two"
            But, if not:
               When n is 3, then:
                  Add result to "Three"
               But, if not:
                  When n is 4, then:
                     Add result to "Four"
                  But, if not:
                     When n is 5, then:
                        Add result to "Five"
                     But, if not:
                        When n is 6, then:
                           Add result to "Six"
                        But, if not:
                           When n is 7, then:
                              Add result to "Seven"
                           But, if not:
                              When n is 8, then:
                                 Add result to "Eight"
                              But, if not:
                                 When n is 9, then:
                                    Add result to "Nine"
                                 But, if not:
                                    Add result to tostring of n
                                 End when
                              End when
                           End when
                        End when
                     End when
                  End when
               End when
            End when
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do

   Remember that filtered is []
   Remember that j is 0
   Do this result's length times:
